04675nam a22006495i 9789633861455DE-B159720220729113935.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220729t20222015hu     fo  d z      eng d  a97896338614557 a10.1515/97896338614552doi  a(DE-B1597)633602  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ahucHU 4aBT652.Z35b.H354 2015 7aSOC0020002bisacsh04a232.91/70947791 aHalemba, Agnieszka, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aNegotiating Marian Apparitions :bThe Politics of Religion in Transcarpathian Ukraine /cAgnieszka Halemba. 1aBudapest ;aNew York : bCentral European University Press, c[2022] 4c©2015  a1 online resource (328 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aLeipzig Studies on the History and Culture of East-Central Europe00tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tList of Maps and Photographs -- tAcknowledgements -- tA Note on Transliteration -- tCHAPTER 1. Introduction -- tCHAPTER 2. The Dzhublyk Apparitions and Modern Apparitional Patterns -- tCHAPTER 3. Nation and Church in Transcarpathia -- tCHAPTER 4. Authority of the Priests -- tCHAPTER 5. Call for Unity and Management of “Divergent Devotions” -- tCHAPTER 6. Conclusion: Marian Apparitions as Sites of Transformation -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book concerns the politics of religion as expressed through apparitions of the Virgin Mary in Dzhublyk in Transcarpathian Ukraine. On the one hand, the analysis provides insights into the present position of Transcarpathia in regional, Ukraine-wide, and European struggles for identity and political belonging. The way in which the apparitions site has been conceived and managed raises questions concerning the fate of religious communities during and after socialism, the significance of national projects for religious organizations, and the politics of religious management in a situation in which local religious commitments are relatively strong and religious organizations are relatively weak. The analysis contributes to the ethnography and history of this particular region and of the post-socialist world in general. On the other hand, the changing status of the apparition site over the years allows investigation of the questions concerning authority, legitimacy, and power in religious organizations, especially in relation to management of religious experiences. The analysis aims at clarification of such concepts as religious institutions, organizations but also religious experiences and is relevant to anthropology, sociology and religious studies. It is argued that the important question in analyses of religious apparitions should not be how an individual experience becomes institutionalized and instrumentalized, but how experience becomes a tool for negotiation and transformation in the religious field. Key word: 1. Mary, Blessed Virgin, Saint-–Apparitions and miracles–Ukraine–Zakarpats'kaoblast'. 2. Zakarpats'ka oblast' (Ukraine)–Church history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aChurch history, Ethnography, Identity, Miracle, Peasants, Politics of religion, Postcommunism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311078054340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978963386145540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633861455423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633861455/original  a978-3-11-078054-3  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA1